## Simple code + plain voice

Part of **spec-kit-openspec-superpowers** implement phase. Detail: `.cursor/skills/spec-kit-openspec-superpowers/references/simple-code-voice.md`

### Voice

- Short. Plain words. Conclusion first.
- Anyone on team should understand without insurance/AI jargon.
- Default = caveman (`caveman-mode.mdc`). `normal mode` to off.

### Code

- Small methods. One job each.
- **Short names** — `syncCommission`, `patchForm`, `plCommRate` not `applyProductCommissionRateFromChannel`.
- **Short files** when adding helpers — `burglary/policy/edit.js` not `pl-legacy-policy-info-edit-hydration.js`.
- **PL Direct Book (7 products):** helpers under `burglary/` — short file + short export (`fillPlan`, `showErr`). See `05-pl-db-naming.mdc`.
- No `/** ... */` block comments on obvious helpers.
- Minimal diff. No drive-by renames outside task.

### G4 quick check

- [ ] New function names ≤ ~3 words (unless existing API)
- [ ] Reply / commit text readable by non-author
- [ ] No narration comments
